<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-84-0940 </DOCNO><TEXT>Although still in its developmental stages, magnetic resonance imaging(MRI) has already made a significant contribution to the field of imaging.MRI is noninvasive and nonradiative and gives tridimensional views; currently,there is no need for contrast material and/or catheterization. Furthermore,in some areas of imaging, MRI may replace computed tomography (CT) and/orultrasound and will therefore be cost effective.</TEXT></DOC>